commit.message:
Issue #1780: Implement a new FSIO handler akin to the `realpath(3)` function, for resolving paths. (#1790)

Most of the time, this will be a pass-through.  However, modules like mod_vroot
play games with filesystem paths, and other modules need a way to play by those
same rules.

commit.message: Issue #1721: Add regression test for parser failure of Include'd files.

configure: Use char ** for the iconv input argument (#1754)

The standard iconv function uses char ** even for the input buffer.
Using the incompatible const char ** type causes the check to fail if
the compiler treats such type errors as errors, instead of merely
warning about it.

tree 5536affdc3e1581dac5f0e76a29f32837ae917a7

configure: Use char ** for the iconv input argument (#1754)

The standard iconv function uses char ** even for the input buffer.
Using the incompatible const char ** type causes the check to fail if
the compiler treats such type errors as errors, instead of merely
warning about it.

commit.message:
Issue #1746: If we fail to resolve the DNS name for the implicit "server config" vhost to an IP address, we need to fail completely on startup. (#1752)

Failure to do so will lead to unexpected null pointer dereferences elsewhere
in modules.
